-- KKR, Permira, Sun European May Bid for Peacocks, Telegraph Says
-- B y   T u h i n   K a r
-- 2012-01-22T07:03:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-22/kkr-permira-sun-european-may-bid-for-peacocks-telegraph-says.html
KKR (KKR)  & Co. LP, Permira and Sun
European Partners LLP are “poised to bid” for Peacocks Stores
Ltd. after Sun European secured a deal to buy the U.K. clothing
retailer’s Bonmarche unit, the Sunday Telegraph reported.  Edinburgh Woollen Mill is leading the list of companies
interested in some of Peacocks’ business, the newspaper
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Tesco Plc (TSCO) 
may bid for some of Peacocks Stores’ estates, the newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tuhin Kar in London at 
